  "texts": [
    "This assembly was 1,198 Mb long, of which 1,192 Mb (93.1% of the predicted genome size based on cytological evidence 34) was anchored to pseudochromosomes (Table 1).",
    "Gene space completeness, assessed using Benchmarking Universal Single-Copy Orthologs (BUSCOs) 35, was >96% for all assemblies.",
    "Importantly, 93.2% of the BUSCO genes were duplicated in the HiFi assembly (Table 1), indicating that most of the gene duplicates from the allopolyploidy event were retained.",
    "The Robusta and Eugenioides genomes contained, respectively, 67.5% and 59.7% TEs (Supplementary Section 3.2), with Gypsy long in 1706, was used to establish Arabica cultivation in the Caribbean in 1723.",
    "Independently, the French cultivated Arabica on the island of Bourbon (presently Réunion) 26, and the descendants of a single plant that survived by 1720 form the contemporary Bourbon group."
  ]
}